  <discussion>Cylindropuntia ×tetracantha (= C. acanthocarpa × C. leptocaulis) is an uncommon
        hybrid; sympatric hybrids long confused with and usually included in C. ×tetracantha involve
        C. leptocaulis × C. spinosior, which have spineless, reddish, and strongly tuberculate
        fruits and long-spreading, subwhorled branches, and C. leptocaulis × C. versicolor, which
        have spineless, reddish, smooth, and enlarged fruits and a less spreading
        habit.</discussion>
